FBIS4-3975 "drchi082_a_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-082 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing Denies Reports on Troop Movements OW2804094094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0931 GMT 28 Apr 94 OW2804094094 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 28 (XINHUA) -- The report about China sending additional 30,000 troops to Sino-Indian border is a "sheer fabrication", Wu Jianmin, a spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, said here today. "Spreading such lies is obviously out of ulterior motives," he said. He told a news briefing that the Governments of China and India signed an agreement on the maintenance of peace and tranquillity along the Line of Actual Control in the border areas last year and have begun talks on the reduction of troops along the Actual Control Line," he said.
